column15: Had steroid injection yesterday, circling. History: circling behaviour, anxiety and increased aggression. Examination: EENT fundic exam normal PLRs intact, constant circlint to left side. Diagnosis: neurologic signs, circling, no obvious cause, little improvement with steroid. Plan: client elects euthanasia over constant signs and poor qol

"Collapsed, near moribund. hasn't eaten for 3 days, drinking. Has gradually been going downhill, quite quiet recently. On presentation, very wobbly BCS 1/9. Brief exam resulted in her lying in lateral recumbency with respiratory distress. Pale MM slightly jaundiced, severe dental disease. HR 200 with murmur RR 42 with marked increase in effort and harsh but dull lung sounds. Small kidneys#. Advised very unwell either euthanase (multiple comorbidities, concerned about organ failure or adverse response to vidalta) or admit for intravenous fluids, work up, bloods etc but suspect she might die or need euthanasia regardless. <<name>> wanted to take her home and had to be quite firm that she could not go home to die as suffering and against my RCVS oath as well as my own ethics. Either euthanasia or treatment. Mr M agrees with me and took some convincing to get Mrs M to understand that welfare issue. Iv catheter placed, pentobarbitone intravenous to effect. Owners taken home to bury"

"Recheck mobility. Mobility worse since last visit, no longer sitting, straight from stand to lying down, occationally leaves dribble of urine where lain. Discussed QOL, O likely to opt to PTS soon, will want housevisit and crem with dignity."
PTS due to QoL as losing weight dramatically. Consent form signed. Owner decided for communal cremation
massive tumour
"severely emaciated now with poor QOL."
"1.90kg. Owner upset will have cat PTS at own practice this afternoon"
all went smoothly.
DOA.  rushed in by owners - thought he may have already passed away. fell out of a 4th storey window. on exam - no heart beat, no pulses, no palebral responce, confirmed that he had passed away.
Vaccine - L4 and KC.  Seen yesterday by LB so did not complete PE. Lovely dog. Vacc given.

Behavioural/neurological changes for about 2 weeks where seems completely not there, freaks out, gets very anxious, starts nibbling. O mentions is getting worse and worse, not able to sleep for a week as even at night it happens. Any sort of noise stimulates it. From description sounds more neurological than behavioural. O wants PTS on welfare grounds as feels he doesn't have a QOL anymore.
"Guinea pig has mass in cr abdo and really obtunded and struggling. Adv euth but is daughters pet and want to take home for her to decide. Adv re opening hours and coming back later today."

"V+++ D- last few days.  V lethargic.  Lost 2kg since end Aug.  NAD chest Hr=120 MM CRT Pulse ok.  NADabdo - v painful cranial abdo tho.  T=37.6.  Eyes ears ok.  DDX: CKD/Liver/cancer etc - all poor prognosis.  Given ~80ml s/c.  Options: Work up bloods/fluids/scan etc or euthanasia.  O opted for Euth - will make appt for tmw.  Payment plan - will pay tmw."

OR no change to regurgitation with meds , had another resp episode and O thinks struggling with resps a bit more cranially now / around throat area. eating and bright but losing weight. disc the options again with O: refer or pTS. no other option currently as have tried and no change. still something more sinister underlying that we are not reaching so far eith diagnostics. not fair to continue trial and error. O udnerstood and concerned regarding QOL anyway - opted for pTs as the kindest more sensible option at this stage. sedated first IM and passed peacefully alongside O via lethal injection IV. owner requested ashes returned for scattering in scatter tube. death confirmed by auscult.

In for discussion on euthanasia. <<identifier>> has been deteriorating rapidly especially in the last 3 days. has lost a lot of condition. been eating only a littel and then bringing it back up. owner just wanted her checked over to ensure they are making the right decision. QAR. diffuse muscle atropy. BCS 3.5/9. mm pale. HM as before. Discuss with owner euthanasia is recommended. she has lost so much condition & being sick constantly. owner's husband is at work so they are going to book in for this evening for PTS. Would like individual cremation & ashes returned.

INCONTINENCE, STROKE- LIKE EVENTS, EUTHANASIA. O reports has been urinary and faecally incontinent for the last few months, also wife/kids have reported stroke-like events quite regularly in this time. O noticed event yesterday. Walking along, back legs non-responsive, couldn't move them, stretching out and truggling to crawl forward. Seemed very distressed. O reports has been eating but frequent vomiting after eating/drinking volume recently. Family have been considering euthanasia recently. have tried various litter trays/substrates to see if will use instead of toiletting indoors but no luck. CE: gums pale pink and moist, cranial lower premolars mild gingivitis, ear tips hairless and skin curled- O reports has been this way for a few years, no swellings, firm dermal mass on neck, not attached to deeper layers, discuss sampling, HR 180 no murmur/dysrhtyyhmia, lung fields nothing abnormal detected, lean body condition, ribs and spine prominent, abdomen- liver enlarged, palpable beyond rib cage, both kidneys symmetrical, bladder small and soft. No obvious masses/thickenings but liver definitely of concern. Normal hindlimb relfexes, no discomfort for manipulation joints, saliva staining and flea dirts/live fleas on dosrum, O has notived lots of licking etc. Discussed further investigation, cost is concern, discussed starting with bloods to screen for renal/liver issues etc and ideally then advance to imaging, O discussed with family and decided would prefer euthanasia as feel she is suffering at home, cannula placed LF 7ml pentoject IV, no heartbeat

"been fit until pased faeces in house overnight, disorientated when owner got up at 6 am, seemed tos ettle, ate breakfast, seizure lasting 2-3 mins later in morning, brought here, is ambulatory but going into corners/ walls. on exam no nystagmus, panting a lot, abdo relaxed, temperature 38.8, discuss differential diagnosis of seizures in older dogs offer bloods or referral if wanted to investigate. decide can't face having more, will put to sleep, discuss crematoria, decide would like pet crem at <<identifier>>, want to take her themselves and want put to sleep at home vets. faxed history to <<identifier>> Vets <<identifier>>."

<<name>>: left eye conjunctivitis. S: owner reports possibly something in her eye, red and inflamed. started beginning of last week. has been watering. not bothering at it. owner icked out some plant material a couple of days ago. otherwise well - Eating, drinking, urinating, defecating normally. O: BAR, mucous membranes pink and moist, capillary refill time 1-2s,thoracic ausc nad, abdo palp nothing abnormal detected. right eye within normal limits.  left eye some conjucntival hyperaemia, no chemosis, ophthalmoscopic exam nad, fluoro negative, no fb found behind third eyelid on exam with cotton bud and local. A: left eye conjunctivitis. PLAN: - chloramphenicol BID for 3 days. - owner to monitor for discharge, spasm, discomfort etc. call if concerned. recheck 3 days if no improvement or sooner if worried.  For External Use Only
Hasn't decided for what is going to happen with her body.
Ate dark chocolate biscuits 1 hour ago, induced emesis , send hoem with charcoal and rv an.
"o/c 3-4d and o/f.  gluc 5 this am. on exam has mid abdomen mass - feels like alimewntary lymphomma/carcinomma. offer investigation. o doesnt want.  required euth.  ]."
RTA.  Right eye prolapsed. mandible fractured.  cat dyspnoea.  lateral recumbency

jsd. O says qol going downhill. problems weeing blood and leaking every day. now sore back end and going to bite him if touches. some days more mobile than others. O says been passing blood in urine about 1 year. Owould like her put to sleep,no investigations. walked in ok. squatting to wee for long time- blood stained small amout. slim overgrown nails. crying/screaming when touched forelimb so muzzled. put to sleep. after felt bladder; really hard mass about 4 cm- mass or impacted bladder stones? also teeth grade 5.

"In today as had fit and owner brought in unconscious. Stick thin and very cold ears and extremities. Brought straight through and placed on oxygen. Non responsive and lying in lateral recumbency. Nasal crusting and yellow discharge+++, and dischare on paws. Urine staining and crusting on bottom, tail and back feet. Sawdust in eyes. Adv put to sleep as can not recover. Around 9weeks old."

"Distended abdo - PTS. Hx - OR that about 3 days ago noticed not quite herself - a little panty and standing funny. notice abdo quite swollen. still very bright in self. EDDU all normal. <<identifier>> the last few days gotton a little worse - not able to move about as well but still very bright and eating as usual. not really doing normal interactions or cleaning though.  Stopped laying about 6 months ago, is 4.5years old.  Ex - BAR. RR 40 and slightly laboursed. HR 300 +. chest sound fine. abdo very distended and difficult to feel anything, though was possibly fluid as possible thrill but no fluid when poped needle in - just lots of negative pressure. tried scanning but could not get adeguate image.  Discussed possibilities with owner - tumour vs cysts vs egg bound (unlikely as stopped laying a while ago). after long discussion about what could do - x-rays, tial with metacam and antibiotics etc O decided that PTS best as although still bright behaviour is not normal and do not want her suffering. O2 chamber to GA then injectioninto brain"
"Hamster died on arrival-. no heartbeat present- loosing urine and faeces- provided nice small white box for owner to collect and take <<name>> in."

Unsteady on Hls for 2-3 days, possible longer. Unable to jump up on bed. Passing tiny pellets of faeces 3-4d, crying when passing faeces yesterday. Was eating really well after op, but reduced appetite last few days. V+ 2 nights ago. Food. 5-6 hours after eaten. V+ 3 times during week prior to this. Would like to pay b4 PTS.

"~3-4mo. Taken on from lady at a show 2wks ago - gave him away for free. O noticed when home that has head tilt, ataxic, possibly blind. Eats well but gets distressed++, and when tried to socialise with another GP both became distressed. On exam, mild waxy discharge from ears, cannot rule out middle /inner ear dz but appears to have multiple neuro deficits, and with age would be suspicious of congenital cause. Offered to trial tx for OM, but O feels he is too distressed and requested pts today."
sedate Sedator 0.2 Ketamine 0.2 im.  the name on the casket"<<name>>"
"unwell cat for several weeks owners instructions are to pts no investigations wanted."

Booster vaccination.  Or defecating, urinating, drinking, eating ok.  Mm pink and moist capillary refill time und er 2 sec.  ent - nothing abnormal detected.  Ln- nothing abnormal detected.  Abdomen soft/comfy.  Hr and respiratory rate in limits.  Ok to vaccinate

Very unwell on Sunday, y'day not eating, today ate a little but thenn had dyspnoiec episode, wet floor. settled, but very lethargic. clinical exam - eyes dull, abdo feels bloated (exam lying down back of car). heart rate 120bpm and regular, congestion on chest, fluid from nose. Mms pale. very little we can do for him without possible surgery if beleed, dont' think palide mms and extreme lthargy due to heart failure as no blue tone and no tlaboured breathing. supsect possible abdominal bleed. euthanasia right choice for <<identifier>>, he looks tired, eyes dull, given u. IV catheter placed, 25mls pentoject given slow IV.
"Not eating, vomiting. O has decided it's time."

"Mother in laws cat who died last week. doesn't get on with Os cats. V thin. large s/c mass R neck and huge thyroid palpable. HR 240bpm. kidneys small. liver small. m wasting over hls - likely OA. Miliary derm over caudal dorsum and tail base. Adv euthanasia - many issues affecting qol."
"removed upper remaining canine and lower incisor, some root might be left. cauterised some of bleeding inflammatory tissue but not much could be removed."
<<name>> O will take home."

Reason: collapsed. Hx: would not get up this am, now walking, gradual decline in demenour, not as happy on walk, o very upset and thinks it is time. Panting lots at night. Exam: walked into consult , wagging tail, bar, mmp ink, LFL mass still present and lame 2/5 on LFL, hr 80, rr panting, abdomen ok, A: suspect mobility issue due to mass on LFL which suspect is neoplastic now. offerrred. 1. pain meds and reassess 24 hours. 2. pts. o came had already made decision to pts. gave acp 3mls i/m. placed iv catheter in RFL and euthanased with pentoject 40mls iv. O very upset. O has neighbour she will talk to today. sent sympathy card.

Mammary lumps/ euthanasia. O reports lumps have grown massively since last time. Still eating and drinking ok but O thinks is in pain. Entire, last season long time ago. QAR, emaciated and dihadreted, nothing abnormal detected chest ausc, abdomen comfortable. - lumps on two last mammary glads, right side - one egg size, irregular and firm, other one: firm and multiple irreg shaped. - left side midway pea size, firm. Disc options again. Disc risks associated with every single option. Disc recovery and prognosis. Disc QOL. O doesn't want to keep her in pain, O elected PTS. Consent form signed. O elected our practice to arrange cremation. O elected communal cremation. IV pento, death confirmed by lack of heart beats.

**WHEN TIME COMES TO PTS OWNER WOULD LIKE ASHES BACK***. Owner tried to taper the medication but the symptoms of struggling to breathe came back. has been to emergency vet but no record of this. Discuss with owner plan going forward: Owner would prefer to medicate as needed for clini9cal signs but not go down the road of diagnotics or surgical intervention. Advuse can up dose of frusedale if needed and to contatc us if he feels thisis needed. Trial rimadyl as hind legs have marked crepitus and he goes off them regularly. Advise repeat prescription policy.

"Presented this am as has been off food for the last couple of days and OR is drinking alot more than normal. Last had a season 2 weeks ago. OR has had vaginal discharge. no v/d, no c/s. Very flat in consult room, PE, thoracic aus nothing abnormal detected, abdo pal painful, temperature 39.2. Have advised O that we need to admit and do bloods and u/s abdo as suspect pyo. O has not got any money and is unable to afford anything and wants to pts. After having spoken to <<identifier>>, agreed that O could sign her over to us. O agreed. O has just called back syaing that he has found someone that will pay for f/i and op, O agreed to come and pay upfront now and then M can be returned to O. O given consernt over the ohine to go ahead and operate as pyo found on abdo u/s. KG witness to phone conversation. Pre-med: ACP 0.69 mls and methadine 0.69 mls IV. Induction: prpofol 11mls IV. ET tube size 10 used, cuffed. Analgesia- 1.39mls meloxaid Sc. Given- 3.49mls Augmentin slow iv and 1.74 mls synuclav mls sc. Midline incision made, right uterine horn very enlarged and pus filled, left uterine horn normal in appearance, both ovaries very enlarged. 2 encircling ligatures placed on both ovarian pedicles in 3m polysorb. 2 transfixing ligatures placed on cervix in 3m polysorb. All stumps cjecked prior to closing no bleeding seen all ligatures secure. Muscle layer closed with 3m maxon simple continuous suture pattern. Sub-cut closed with 3m biosyn simple continuous suture pattern. Skin closed with intradermals-3m biosyn. To go home with synuclav oral tablets and oral meloxaid to start tomorrow. To wear a bc at all times and to be fully rested with lead walks to toilet only for the next week. POC in 3 and 10 days time."
"deteriorated, gone downhill."

"<<identifier>> was seen at start of week for dehydration and lethargy. Did not stay in for hospitalisation - O syringe fed and water at home.  Back in again today, very flat and non responsive. O says has been twitching at home this morning.  Clinical exam: HR 60, RR 8, mms white, no CRT, Temp - no registering on thermometer, checked twice. So flat and non responsive discussed options for hospitalisation, but feel she is too weak to make a dramatic recovery at this point. Offered PTS, O agreed.  PTS carried out today. Did not want cat carrier - left in practice with us. Has not yet made a decision - will keep <<identifier>> for next 7 days till O phones with decision."
very weak, not moving, purulent vaginal discharge

"Really deteriorating. lost 3kg, OR not eating today, has only had a small amount of chicken, has some days when he does eat well OR. Very subdued today. Very painful on palpation of jaw, swollen on R side suspect tumour now infiltrated madibular bone. Foul smelling, purulent bloody material from mouth, tumour necrotic inside mouth. Mild crackles on ausculation of lungs, mucopurulent discharge from nose. Strongly adv PTS, in pain and suffering now. O feels she needs her partner to be there so has booked an appt for tomorrow. O says that she hasn't looked at the mass, showed her in consult. Adv pain relief and antibiotics, o intimated that she may not come in tomorrow if <<location>> is eating, adv PTS in any case as so painful, disp meds for a few days in case o does not bring him in as do not want him to suffer. given meloxaid and synuclav injs. oral meds to start tomorrow.  Next appointment WITHIN 5 days - o has appt for tomorrow for PTS which I strongly advised should be kept."
mouth is a little better and dog is able to eat but condition is terminal so euthanasia when no longer enjoying life

Weight loss recently & has a fur ring trapped around penis. Bleeding from tip of penis also. O thinks he is urinating. Eating & drinking ok but very lethargic. Penis protruding & tip is necrotic with pus discharging from lesions on tip. Unable to replace conscious. Very thin & very lethargic here. Advised PTS due to poor prognosis
"forget me not contacted.  owner will call forget me not directly to sort which casket would like"
"old rabbit, going downhill, skin and bones, hudge lump on left side chest. this morning was laying for 4 h on the side and twiching. agreed kinder to let him go."

RIGHT HIND10/10 lame much worse now infected/necrotic wound lateral hock swollen from toes to hock alse small necrotic lesion near prepuce does sit near radiator but no evidence how he got these wounds - not been fighting.  advise euthase on humane grounds. can only pay 1/2 today rest by 20th jan so done payment agreement
"Resp distress, passing blood from cloaca and head on one side, eyes closed. Disc ddx with o and offered trial tx or referral vs PTS."
all went smoothly

Anal gland carcinoma most likely, owner cannot afford any treatment and animal staying with previous partner that cannot look after her and refuses to take her to the PDSA. Painful, welfare issues. Owner ellected PTS for welfare reasons. - Changed their mind. Meds to keep her comfortable and highly recommended to take he to the pdsa as elligible. Gentleman agreed. ddx: chronic anal gland abscess, anal furunculosis, anal gland carcinoma.

BLOCKED BLADDER - PTS. OR <<identifier>> has been v uncomfortable, thinks possibly constipation. Some D+ coming from bottom. Uses litter tray indoors, F+ reduced output. Seems very painful in abdomen, growling++ and hissing which O says is very unlike her. Active abdominal effort seen. On palpation of abdo can feel bladder is v firm. Smell of U+ around her also. Suspect she is blocked to some degree +/- F+ issues also. Option to have in and try and treat for potential blockage - pain relief +/- catherisation which would require sedate/GA. In light of Mollys other issues, O has decided to PTS. Agree with decision - seems in pain now and with multiple other issues think its the right time. IVC placed, taken to consult for O to spend some time. 5ml Pentoject injected, passed away peacefully in carrier with O present. * Cremation and <<identifier>> in scatter tube please *. * O requested fur clip - sent in sympathy card *

Acute onset head tilt and circling to RHS last 24hours. Gradual weight loss noted over recent weeks, although is still eating. On CE very depressed mentation, eyes barely open, sluggish movements but headtilt to RHS and gradually circling. Severe paresis of hindlimbs, worse in right hind. suspect CNS event, either stroke or neoplasia. QOL very poor and prognosis extremely guarded/hopeless. Advise PTS as QOL unacceptable. O initially very shocked, spoke with husband. Very upset, but after some discussion did come to understand kindest thing for <<name>>. Husband agrees with decision to PTS. Went smoothly. Home burial.

Have you, or anyone in your household, had signs of <<name>> 19 or a positive <<name>> test within the last 21 days? no. Have you returned from abroad and been instructed to quarantine within the last 14 days? no. Are you categorised as <<name>> risk? no. Have you been instructed to self isolate for any other reason? no. history. old, incontinence, not eating. decided on euthanasia. clinical exam. recumbent, BCS 1/9. azotaemic smell, rapid respiration. prognosis grave. socially distanced indoor euthanasia.  home burial
"not improved with medication. No proprioception on left front leg. Not able to exercise just laying down all day. Agrred QoL no good and pts best decision."

"Very old and very arthritic, also very overweight with significant muscke waste but still copping ok. Meds the only thing that keeps him going, OR on borrowed time anyway so ok to repeat meds as normal."

<<name>> - Bit brighter Sat but since been much the same. Further weight loss. Melaena and fresh blood. Off food. Bilateral red eye IOP L 13mm/Hg, R 10mmHg. Owner has decided on euthanasia rather than referral or other options

"Rushed in as emergency - seen at Easipet 4 weeks ago as thought poisoned but bloodswere apparently ok. Sounds like had seizure this morning - collapsed and urinated. Lateral collapse, unresponsive, blink present, HR 120 regular ,no murmur RR 36 T 35.2. Apparently has been PP/PD but very thin. Advise hospitalisation and monitoring but O decided euth as given very poor prognosis"
deterioration over weekend. Time has come.
"WAS Sick a little night before last. was digging holes. lying in plant pots. massive deterioration in last hour. brough in moribund."

being looked after by sister / friend. presented with lethargy, inappetance, vomiting, excessive PDPU: cannot get medication in. findings consistent with renal impairment. discussed euthanasia. carer to speak with owner

"brought in by owners sister. OR been unwell for some time not eating for 3 days,  Pe MM plae pink CRT <2, Ln's WNL chest asuc noraml Hr130, nothing abnormal detected on abdominal palpation. goiter palatable. offerd T4 test and mirtrazipine in mean time owner decied PTS best option, consented over phone.  owners sister signed form."
"pt been licking and biting feet for the past few week. large interdigital lesions. pt has lost more weight and looking very uncomfortable. Advised PTS."

"vomiting last 5 days- intermittent 4-5 times daily. last 4 weeks- occ faecal incontinance- very loose motions- does have treats/different foods. diarrhoea - black in colour- malaena -.  more lethargic in self.  episode this morning- collapse. disucssed poor prognosis-.  systemic lymphadenopathy. pre paying for euthanasia tomorrow"

Vet:<<name>> Problem: rectal prolapse. O came in this evening to find that his rectum has prolapsed, brought straight down. BAR, nothing abnormal detected on exam other than severe rectal prolapse, 20cm of tissue prolapsed and extremely damaged, turning necrotic. Plan: disucssed with O admit and surgery tomorrow vs PTS, ran through what surgery would likely entail, costs involved risk of complications etc, O discussed amongst themselves with myself out of the room as well, decided to PTS as feel that would be too much to put him through, aware would want investigations after recovered to identify and treat underlying cause as well and feel would be too much for him. Advsied is fair decision, brought him back in for them to say goodbye having put IV cannula in in prep, Mr stayed while PTS performed with 5ml IV pentoject, death confirmed by lack of heartbeat, taking home to bury.

"off food hand feeding etc ate last pm struggling to get up panting facial swelling and stridor cand complere oral exam t 39.5 cvs resp[ ok admit bloods sedat/ga and ex mouth est 30 for bloods and ga.  Lab Request References Generated: Haematology (3 Part) is 011646. Electrolytes Profile is 011646. Comprehensive Panel is 011646. enlarged tonsisl s mand popliteal glands lymphoma adv owner o req pts"

"chicken sensitive stays, but shes V+ everything else. drinking fine, o uses lactose free milk in addition. D+ 5 days ago. today stools urine fine, but lethargic. Cx - massive dehydration, massive weight loss (2.2 kg since May) bright in herself, but wobbly when moving. disscussed possible problems (CKD, hyperthyroidism, other?). advised 2 options. 1)admit for hosp and workup. 2)PTS. after disscussion O opts for PTS at home, will make an app."

"Been eating but struggling and salivating in the last 5 days. Today O seen blood through the saliva and not eating.  V messy around mouth. Not allowing inspection but unable to close mouth. Advise sedation.  Large tumour at base of tounge - advise euthanasia."

"quick chat regarding QoL. mass has now ulcerated, Chalkie not happy any more. not sleeping at night, pacing and sometimes crying. discussed and offered - 1) Sx tomorrow - but we have already discussed the risks etc, or PTS. PTS booked in for wed, with myself only please."

O brought Moppet in - lethargic and almost unresponsive. minimal reflex, arithmia. advise O that we need to rush as beliveed cat was entering first stages of death. OR has had cats before and went very bad before death, decided for us to do PTS without her present.  cat was in bad shape, no muscle, no tonus, no available blood vessels, decided better to inject organs.  unable to locate a kidney - no bladder, no gut content. Injected IC - no reaction from animal. Instant effect. <<identifier>>: 08.50 AM

Femela rabbit. entire. not up to date with vacs. No more rabbits at home. O noticed not eating for past 2 days. Blood in feces. No diarrhoea but some hard and soft faeces (caecotroph)? CE.  mucous membrane pale moist. rr 92 increased exp effort. hr200. T 33. Fresh blood from vulva, none in anus. days. adenocarcinoma, pyometra, RVHD. Discussed <<name>> O guarded prognosis and old rabbit: offered hosp and stabilization/ imaging or. pts
"HPC INFORMED. Sympathy card sent."
Reminders removed. Sympathy card request sent
Sudden onset epistaxis this morning. Dead on arrival. No audible heartbeat and no plr. Ventral mass may have eroded through major bloodvessel? O taking home for bural
"Came in as emergency, acutely collapsed, mm white"
"OR still really struggling to get around. Still eating but otherwise thinks QOL very limited. Discussed about different pain releif options and using in combination as well but O decided pts."
"weight loss. Gone completely off legs since saturday. All in agreement that put to sleep kindest option now. please call owner when askhes come back"
terminal kidney failure

"Odour from vulval area, also vocalising a lot and arching her back. Eating normally, bright, passing normal faecal pellets. CE: BAR mmembs pink Food in mouth. Chest ausc: NAD. Vulva - very inflamed, swollen, perineal skin shows urine scald++. Firm caudal abdominal mass, uneven/ lumpy, 5cm in length. ? bladder/ uterine mass, could even be urolith. Wgt loss. Discuss: options are investigate with imaging to see whether urolith ( and therefore, any hope of tx) Feel prog v guarded, O opted for euthanasia. Took to Dignity for individual cremation."

owner brought in as feels dog deteriorating. rapid weight loss, blind. vomiting now.  thirst normal. diarrhoea with blood.  BCS 2/9.  2/6 murmur. lungs clear abdo palp no abnormality detected.  discussion re quality of life - owner feels that this is not present at the moment and would like euth.  sedated prior to euth as dog disorientated

recheck. no eaten or drank, stayed in bed all night. not urinated or defacted. stood up ad kept truning around, arched back. had pain releif overnight, t40.5. or not himself at all, sitting in bed and depressed. temperature 40.5, abdo palp very sore and tense.  discussed needs bloods and hops at minight, worried re temperature. o worried re pain and not geting better. advised does take time in this. o worried as no gauraantee. long dicussion about options, o worried about QOL and o opted for PTS. after pts gums very yellow, ears and nose yellow, pts with o presnet, ch held, catheter placed in prep

"Presented as was circling yesterday, and rolling in cage now. O brought in for assessment. On PE noted rolling involuntary - cannot open eyes, non-responsive to stimulus, etc. Discussed options - PTS."

Recheck ( PTS). OR he has eaten on saturday a bit of chicken and after that he deteriorated quiqly, vomiting a lot of times and today he is very lethargic. dog presented flat and depressed. T37.4. hr 130. mm pale pink.  abdominal pain present on palpation. chest ausc Nad , femural pulse. Judging on bloods taken friday he is in end stage kidney failure the least. Adv O that he has 2 options. One we admit him and after the end of schedule we transfer him to NE and try intensive care on him but the prognosis is very guarded or we pts. O talked to the wife for 5 minutes outside and decided to PTS. placed RC cathether and after injected 10 ml iv of pentoject O present.

"O came in to discuss Woody, he is suffering now, lethargic and not keen to do anything, will eat if hand fed but otherwise not interested and was crying in pain last night. Marked submandib swelling, large firm masses palpable with oedematous swelling aswell - neoplastic spread.  Time to pts but o would like house visit on sat am so family can say goodbye, advise increase tramadol in meantime to 2 caps up to three times per day but phone for pts sooner if in any distress.  Has requested private cremation, in scatter box."

Dead on arrival. Brought straight down after phoning practice, not breathing. Was out for a walk around <<location>> Valley; playing fetch with a stick, collapsed, rigid and stopped breathing. O attempted CPR immediately before bringing <<location>> straight down. Dead when <<location>> arrived. cold periphery, cyanotic MM. not yet in rigor, suspect had died at the time O phoned us. Informed O. Understandably in shock and very upset. Allowed O time with <<location>>. Discussed possible causes, but adv'd would only be able to determine with Post Mortem. Offered this, but O has declined, would rather not known cause. Discussed home burial and cremation options after some time. O wants cremation but unsure if communal or private. O wants to discuss tonight at home and phone tomorrow with decision. O may come down tomorrow to see <<location>> one more time and wrap him in his own blanket. Expl'd will be kept in cold storage over night, so will need to give us some time to prepare him, and warned he will still be very cold when they do visit. O seems understanding

. Straining and passing blood, very distressed with bottom and freq pints of day. Cannot palpate a mass but dog so difficult to deal with. Given heart and kidney disease I would like <<name>> to consider euthanasia on welfare grounds
